commText: Welcome back. PBKS have their impact player - Prabhsimran Singh in, Arshdeep out. Chahar has the new-ball. Two slips in.

Rahul Chahar: The pitch is holding a bit, especially when there was no dew. The speed at which I bowl, I was backing myself to turn it at pace and make it difficult to hit me. I backed myself and knew if I bowled my best ball, they won’t be able to hit. (On plans to Dhoni) I didn’t want to bowl it fuller to him, he hits it well if you push it fuller. I think we conceded about 8-10 runs more than what we started with, but this is still a good target to chase down. We need to play good cricketing shots. I think this, and my performance in the 2019 final are amongst my best spells in the IPL. Both came at the same venue.

Pace vs spin in CSK innings Pace: 2/124 in 12 overs (RR 10.33) Spin: 4/33 in 8 overs (RR 4.13) 4.13 - best ER for spinners in an innings this season while the ER differential of 6.20 is the highest for spin over pace this IPL
CSK innings progression Overs 1-6: 55/0 (RR 9.17) Overs 7-15: 47/3 (RR 5.22) Overs 16-20: 60/4 (RR 12.00)

21:26 Local Time, 15:56 GMT, 21:26 IST: CSK make 162. PBKS will be very happy with this. The powerplay was a good one for CSK as they did not lose a wicket and the platform was set. But as soon as the spinners came, the brakes were applied. Rahul Chahar and Harpreet Brar bossed the middle overs and did not concede a boundary. The left-arm spinner got Rahane and Dube in the same over. Chahar got Jadeja who was promoted to 4. CSK brought in their impact sub - Rizvi who played a laboured innings before he was out. At the other end seeing all this was Gaikwad who nudged around and then went on to complete his fifty. The end overs acceleration too did not come and PBKS restrict CSK to 162. The pitch has bounce and turn for the spinners and CSK have Jadeja and Mo. Even game at this moment, back for the chase in 5 minutes...

Arshdeep Singh to Dhoni, out Dhoni Run Out!! 1 run completed. Dhoni out for the first time this IPL. And it's a run-out. A low full-toss outside off, Dhoni throws the bat at that, flies off the outside-edge, Harshal at short third man drops it, burst through his hands, but recovers and Dhoni is caught well short on the 2nd. He was struggling to make it, shows his age and fitness as he fails to make it. The Dhoni of 5-6 years ago would have comfortably made it, not now. Dhoni run out (Harshal Patel/Jitesh Sharma) 14(11) [4s-1 6s-1]
Arshdeep Singh to Dhoni, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!
Run-out check sent upstairs. Has Dhoni been done here? Yes.

Arshdeep Singh to Dhoni, no run, dug in short on the stumps, quick bouncer, Dhoni pulls and misses, wants to check the height but it's fine. Precious dot
I0$. It's him all the way to face this over.
Arshdeep Singh to Dhoni, no run, I0$ And a direct-hit would have got Mitchell. Dhoni toe-ends the low full-toss to deep cover, Dhoni was screaming at Mitchell who almost ran 2, the throw misses

Big call to give Chahar the ball in the 19th over. Harshal has bowled just one over. Sam Curran not afraid to go the unconventional route. Chahar against MSD! Who will win?

What's all this noise at Chepauk? Wonder who has walked out to bat - I0$. Ahead of Mitchell. Again the crowd go nuts. A cacophony of noise as the fans have their mobile torches on. It's madness out here and it won't stop till the demigod to many is out there.

No boundaries in middle overs (7-15) in IPL since 2011 PWI vs KKR Pune 2012 RCB vs RPS Pune 2017 RR vs MI Sharjah 2021 CSK vs PK Chennai 2024 *

Rabada to Sameer Rizvi, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! Good sliding catch at third man. Dug in short outside off, Sameer Rizvi ramps it and does not get it fine, Harshal gets across and slides to take it well. End of a laboured innings. Sameer Rizvi c Harshal Patel b Rabada 21(23) [4s-1]

It's been 42 balls since the last boundary.

Time for the strategic break. PBKS have pulled things back remarkably - 30 for 3 in the last 7 overs, all bowled by spin and they've left CSK choking. This ain't a 200-run wicket, but the hosts will need at least 150 to stay competitive

Rahul Chahar to Jadeja, out Lbw!! RJ has been given OUT LBW . He's almost on his way, but he turns back towards his captain. Gaikwad runs all the way and they decide to review. No bat and this leg-break struck him in front of middle and leg. It's spinning and even umpire's call would be enough for Chahar. Onto ball-tracking: It's three reds, crashing into leg and CSK have burned both reviews. RJ is OUT. The hosts finding themsleves in a pickle now, RJ was looking to nudge this to the on-side and ended up playing all around the line, the impact was inh front of middle and it would've struck leg. RJ goes and he takes away CSK's second review with him as well. Jadeja lbw b Rahul Chahar 2(4)

Harpreet Brar is the first conventional left-arm finger spinner to dismiss Shivam Dube in IPL since 2022.

Harpreet Brar to Shivam Dube, out Lbw!! Dube has been given OUT LBW, the umpire thought long, but not Dube, he reviews immediately. Is this ball sliding down leg? Or is high enough, was shaping for the big sweep and missed. Looks like no bat and UltraEdge confirms it. Struck on the back-thigh which was bent, onto ball-tracking: This looks close and it's three reds, Dube is OUT. A first-ball dismissal for Dube and PBKS are cock-a-hoop, tossed up on leg and the ball straightened onto the left-hander, Dube was shaping for the mow over mid-wicket and missed, the ball was crashing into the top of middle and it's curtains for the big hitter tonight. Brar slows down the pace and then got the ball to drift across the right-hander - Rahane couldn't get on top of the bounce as he shaped for the slog-sweep, a massive top-edge, Rossouw has plenty of time to run in, settle and complete a reverse-cupped catch.
